The pathogenicity of coronaviruses is highly correlated with the immune dysregulation and the inflammatory response that is triggered by viral particles in the respiratory tract (
 Channappanavar and Perlman, 2017; 
 Huang et al., 2020). Hence, various authors have proposed the therapeutic use of mesenchymal stem cells (MSC) known for their broad immunomodulatory and multipotent differentiating features.
